Package: RPyGeo
Type: Package
Title: ArcGIS Geoprocessing in R via Python
Version: 0.9.3
Date: 2011-09-07
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexander", "Brenning", , "alexander.brenning@uni-jena.de", c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Fabian", "Polakowski", , "fabian.polakowski@gmail.com", role = "aut")
    )
Description: Provide access to (virtually any) ArcGIS Geoprocessing
        tool from within R by running Python geoprocessing scripts
        without writing Python code or touching ArcGIS.
        Requires ArcGIS >=9.2, a suitable version of Python
        (for ArcGIS 9.2: Python 2.4; for ArcGIS 10.0: 2.6), and Windows.
License: GPL-3
LazyData: TRUE
Depends: 
        reticulate (>= 1.2)
Imports:
        shapefiles, 
        RSAGA
SystemRequirements: Windows, Python (>= 2.4.0), ArcGIS (>= 9.2)
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat
